Perform the following checks.


1. Explanation clarity

Check whether compliance_assessment clearly explains how the requirement is addressed.

Mark Unclear if wording is vague.

If unclear, mention the pointer or topic.


2. Commentary completeness

Compare regulatory_information and compliance_assessment
at the highest pointer level.

If one or more requirement pointers appear missing,
mark Partially Clear or Unclear.

In reason, mention the missing pointer label if visible,
otherwise mention the topic.


3. Support for conclusion

Check whether the conclusion is supported by evidence.

If a pointer is not supported,
mention that pointer or topic.


4. Reference traceability

Check whether the evidence reference is specific.

Mark Unclear if reference is generic.

Examples:
policy name only
no section cited
no clause
no date
no version


5. Follow-up clarity (only if Non-Compliant / Partial / Adverse)

If status is Non-Compliant / Partial / Adverse,
check return_to_compliance_plan.

If action is unclear,
mention the pointer or topic.

If status is Compliant → Not Applicable.



